div.div: Mahna Mahna and The Two Snowths

Initially I planned to just get the missing resource space-template_res-bold_desc-brain_T1w , but then it got longer needing space-template_desc-bold_mask as well down the workflow.
Oh, cool, I'm glad the same existing nodeblock builds both! Is there a better way than to check for one of these resource and calling the nodeblock? I mean like adding "The call" in any higher level functions? I'm not sure if it would work, but you might be able to do something like if strat_pool.check_rpool('space-template_res-bold_desc-brain_T1w'): outputs = {} (2 more lines were trimmed) at the top of the warp_timeseries_to_T1template_abcd definition of and then outputs.update({ 'space-template_desc-preproc_bold': (extract_func_brain, 'out_file'), (3 more lines were trimmed) instead of assigning to outputs at the end.

This is replicating https://github.com/FCP-INDI/C-PAC/blob/03a503c0370fa9915b9b841b0bd96e7eda3aa95b/CPAC/func_preproc/func_preproc.py#L1312-L1338? As far as I can tell https://github.com/FCP-INDI/C-PAC/blob/03a503c0370fa9915b9b841b0bd96e7eda3aa95b/CPAC/func_preproc/func_preproc.py#L1296-L1306 is the only nodeblock that outputs 'space-template_res-bold_desc-brain_T1w' and https://github.com/FCP-INDI/C-PAC/blob/03a503c0370fa9915b9b841b0bd96e7eda3aa95b/CPAC/registration/registration.py#L3716-L3748 is the only one that uses that resource as an input. Instead of duplicating the method, why don't we just make sure bold_mask_anatomical_resampled always runs (and runs before warp_timeseries_to_T1template_abcd ) if warp_timeseries_to_T1template_abcd is going to run?
